<img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  I'm sure Ganzo will back me up on this...</span><hr size=1> A lot of you wonder how to make your warrior.  Always put all into STA and left over points into AGI.  You want the most AC/HP you can possibly get.  STR does affect how hard you hit and all, but whats the point of hitting hard when you can survive the fight? = ).  Recently i made a gnome warrior.  My friend who is an ogre warrior lvl 52 made fun of me so bad. I PLed gnome warrior to lvl 51 my mage friend and druid friend helped (took a few weeks).  ME and ogre friend who is a lvl higher and has discipline dueld each other.  I whomped his muther fuckin ass like there was no tomorrow.  I lost...about 2 bubbles hp? which is...ummm...diddly crap?  Of course i was hopping around and all, which warriors are supposed to do.  But with toe to toe fighting Ogre would kick my ass anyday.  But when are you ever gonna do that?  Maybe in a GM event, but who knows.  Warriors are supposed to be real tough and take a lot of hits.  If i got my gnomes 255 STA 255 AGI unbuffed and only 100 STR i bet i could still easily beat any warrior even Furor from FoH (if i had those stats that is heh).  I see a lot of topics &quot;How to make a dark elf warrior&quot;.  My main was a 52 cleric and he had 162 STR unbuffed was a dorf cleric.  My rogue friend who is pretty decked out at lvl 37 has 171 STR WITH his mrylo arm proc (dunno if he can proc it yet, but he is always casting soemthing so im guessing).  He has more then me, but im a cleric with a bunch of wis and mana and resist gear and @#%$ nothing very STR oriented not even TBB.  i had 162 he had 171...only 9 STR difference and he had like ravenscale and stuff he wasnt that twinked out at all and he was a wood elf.  So the high end items will boost your STR up big time.  And also dont forget about buffs either guys...they really help tons.  I retired my boring non fun cleric for a high action ass kicking warrior and i dont regret it in the least.  And the fact that i am a pimpin sexy gnome makes it all the more fun.  Well i gotta go now im tired and wont even remember that i typed this or what i typed in the morning so bye everyone.  STA LEFTOVER INTO AGI...you want AC/HP to live...STR is easy to get and it only makes your DMG higher, but a somewhat low dmging warrior with high AC/HP will do a lot better then a high dmg warrior low AC/HP.  And even at high lvls, warriors generally do the same amount of damage, with ogres and tolls and barbs of course doing more and crap, but warriors are warriors and i dunno what the @#%$ im talking about bye. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior>The Steel Warrior</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena>The Arena</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.steelwarrior.org">The Steel Warrior website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://www.free-irewards.com/cgi-bin/ezboard/games.html?id=ouuIcESe" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/banners/iRewards120x30-08.gif"></a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><IMG SRC="http://service.bfast.com/bfast/serve?bfmid=7279965&siteid=33932331&bfpage=expertc_tax" BORDER="0" WIDTH="1" HEIGHT="1" NOSAVE >
